1.title: Episode #3.1
1.plot: Carissa Walford chats to Chris Hemsworth and Mark Ruffalo about the latest Thor instalment, George Clooney joins forces with Matt Damon for a sinister suburban comedy and we hit the World Premiere of Margot Robbie's latest flick.

2.title: Episode #3.2
2.plot: Mila Kunis, Kristen Bell and Kathryn Hahn talk to us about Bad Mom 2, we go behind-the-scenes of the horror JIGSAW, and chat to the stars who saddle up for My Little Pony The Movie.

3.title: Episode #3.3
3.plot: We catch up with Detroit stars Will Poulter and Anthony Mackie, Johnny Depp, Michelle Pfeiffer and Willem Dafoe talk to us about their stylish new Agatha Christie remake and we chat to the stars of Ben Stiller's latest comedy Brad's Status.

4.title: Episode #3.4
4.plot: We're joined by the stars of Justice League about the superhero bonanza; Nicole Kidman and Colin Farrell team up for a twisted revenge saga; And Will Ferrell and Mark Wahlberg chat to us in LA at the premiere of Daddy's Home 2.

5.title: Episode #3.5
5.plot: This week on Movie Juice we hop over to London and catch up with the stars of Paddington 2, Margot Robbie chats to us about her new film Goodbye Christopher Robin and Will Ferrell and Mark Wahlberg join forces again for Daddy's Home 2.

6.title: Episode #3.6
6.plot: This week on Movie Juice we hit the red carpet for the premiere of Pixar's latest movie Coco, Julia Roberts reveals all about her inspirational new film Wonder and hear the story of Christmas from the animal's point of view - in The Star.

7.title: Episode #3.7
7.plot: This week we hit the red carpet for the premiere of Pitch Perfect 3, chat to the stars of The Disaster Artist plus go behind the scenes of the hugely anticipated new Star Wars film and get the latest on the new Romper Stomper drama series.

8.title: Episode #3.8
8.plot: This week we sit down with John Cena to discuss Ferdinand, get the low down from the stars of Paddington 2, catch up with the cast of inspirational story, Breathe and we feel the force as the saga continues in Star Wars: The Last Jedi.

9.title: Episode #3.9
9.plot: This week we go behind the scenes with Dwayne Johnson of Jumanji Welcome to the Jungle, Matt Damon shows us that big isn't always better in Downsizing, chat with the cast of Coco and check out Hugh Jackman's musical The Greatest Showman.

10.title: Episode #3.10
10.plot: We catch up with the cast of 'The Shape of Water', get the low down on the final film in the Maze Runner saga - 'Maze Runner: The Death Cure' and go behind the scenes on Mark Wahlberg's latest thriller - 'All the Money in The World'

11.title: Episode #3.11
11.plot: This week we come to you from the LA premiere of hilarious road trip comedy 'Father Figures', chat to Margot Robbie about 'I Tonya', plus sit down with Gerard Butler and "50 Cent" to discuss the gritty LA crime saga 'Den of Thieves'

12.title: Episode #3.12
12.plot: Carissa Walford brings you all the action this week from the 'I, Tonya' Australian Premiere plus sits down with the Margot Robbie for a chat. Alicia Malone hangs out with the cast of 'Father Figures' and we check out 'Molly's Game'

13.title: Episode #3.13
13.plot: This week Clint Eastwood talks about his true-life action thriller The 15:17 To Paris, we check out Phantom Thread, go behind the scenes on Insidious: The Last Key and get up close and personal with the cast of Fifty Shades Freed.

14.title: Episode #3.14
14.plot: Maude Garrett sits down with the cast of Marvel Studios' latest addition, Black Panther. We chat to Jake Gyllenhaal about the story, Stronger and check out Saoirse Ronan in her brilliant lead role in the coming of age comedy, Lady Bird.

15.title: Episode #3.15
15.plot: We bounce over to the LA for the 'Peter Rabbit' Premiere, sit down with the cast of the new comedy 'Game Night'. Look at the new dark-comedy 'Gringo' and Aussie brothers The Spierig's are back with another fright-fest called 'Winchester'

16.title: Episode #3.16
16.plot: We check out all the latest premieres from around the world, catch up with the cast of action spy thriller Red Sparrow, go behind the scenes on the new Tomb Raider and get all the details on British biopic Film Stars Don't Die in Liverpool.

17.title: Episode #3.17
17.plot: We head over to LA for the premiere of A Wrinkle In Time, sit down with Chris Hemsworth to get all the details on his new role in 12 Strong plus we get the low down from Colin Firth and Rachel Weisz on the remarkable true-story The Mercy.

18.title: Episode #3.18
18.plot: We chat to Alicia Vikander and the rest of the cast of the new Tomb Raider, have a laugh with Shane Jacobson over his latest comedy plus check out the political comedy 'The Death of Stalin' and the powerful documentary, 'Human Flow'.

19.title: Episode #3.19
19.plot: We catch up with the star-studded gang of the all-time favorite kid's book 'Peter Rabbit', chat to the cast of 'Pacific Rim: Uprising', Rooney Mara tells the untold story of 'Mary Magdalene' and we head to LA for the premiere of 'Gringo'.

20.title: Episode #3.20
20.plot: This week we check out the new coming-out comedy 'Love, Simon', take a vivid trip across the universe in 'A Wrinkle in Time', look at Stephen Spielberg's new sci-fi adventure 'Ready Player One' and have a laugh at the new comedy 'Blockers'.

21.title: Episode #3.21
21.plot: We check out the making of 'Isle of Dogs', look at Emily Blunt's latest horror 'A Quiet Place', sit down with an all-star cast who lend their voices to the Iron Age animation 'Early Man' and Johnny Depp is on the case in 'Sherlock Gnomes'.

imdb.title: Movie Juice
plot: MOVIE JUICE goes behind the scenes of the latest films, from the biggest Hollywood blockbusters to the local indie flicks. Weekly episodes showcase the hottest release movies and feature interviews with actors and directors.::Context Media
